### Product API - HTTP Client Test File
### Use this with REST Client VS Code extension

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@organizationId = org-test-123
@storeId = store-test-456
@productId = 

###
### 1. GET ALL PRODUCTS WITH PAGINATION
###
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products?page=1&limit=10
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

###
### 2. GET PRODUCTS WITH FILTERS (platform & search)
###
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products?page=1&limit=10&platform=shopee&is_active=true&search=laptop
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

###
### 3. SEARCH PRODUCTS
###
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/search?q=gaming
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}

###
### 4. GET ACTIVE PRODUCTS ONLY
###
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/active
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

###
### 5. GET PRODUCTS BY PLATFORM
###
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/platform/shopee
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

###
### 6. CREATE PRODUCT
###
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

{
  "name": "Laptop Gaming ASUS ROG",
  "product_id": "asus-rog-g14-2024",
  "platform": "shopee",
  "key": "laptop-gaming-asus",
  "is_active": true,
  "variants": [
    {
      "variant_id": "var-1",
      "name": "Intel i7 RTX 4070",
      "product_key": "i7-4070",
      "price": 15000000,
      "quantity": 50,
      "discount": 10,
      "finalPrice": 13500000,
      "SKU": "ASUS-ROG-G14-001",
      "GTIN": "1234567890123"
    },
    {
      "variant_id": "var-2",
      "name": "Intel i9 RTX 4080",
      "product_key": "i9-4080",
      "price": 18000000,
      "quantity": 30,
      "discount": 15,
      "finalPrice": 15300000,
      "SKU": "ASUS-ROG-G14-002",
      "GTIN": "1234567890124"
    }
  ]
}

### @name CreateProductResponse
###
### 7. GET PRODUCT BY ID
###
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

###
### 8. UPDATE PRODUCT
###
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}
Content-Type: application/json
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

{
  "name": "Laptop Gaming ASUS ROG Updated",
  "is_active": true,
  "variants": [
    {
      "variant_id": "var-1",
      "name": "Intel i7 RTX 4070",
      "product_key": "i7-4070",
      "price": 14500000,
      "quantity": 60,
      "discount": 12,
      "finalPrice": 12760000,
      "SKU": "ASUS-ROG-G14-001"
    }
  ]
}

###
### 9. BULK UPDATE PRODUCT STATUS
###
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products/bulk-update-status
Content-Type: application/json
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

{
  "product_ids": ["productId1", "productId2", "productId3"],
  "is_active": false
}

###
### 10. SOFT DELETE PRODUCT
###
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

###
### 11. RESTORE DELETED PRODUCT
###
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}/restore
x-organization-id: {{organizationId}}
x-store-id: {{storeId}}

###
### NOTES
###
### - Replace {{productId}} with actual product MongoDB ID after create
### - Replace {{organizationId}} and {{storeId}} with actual IDs
### - Use REST Client extension for VS Code to run these requests
### - Each request separated by ### comment
### - Save response to variables using @name comment
